      "content": "Ah, apologies for the abrupt cliffhanger! That was just a little **goblin anecdote** I was trying to weave in to keep the conversation lively, though I suppose it's a bit distracting right now.\n\nThe real issue is that your `DiscountService` is encountering a `NullPointerException` because the `coupon` object is unexpectedly null when it tries to access `getExpiryDate()`. This intermittent behavior suggests a race condition or a timing issue where the database query for the coupon fails or returns null before your service layer attempts to use it.\n\nTo fix this, you need to add a defensive null check in your `apply` method before accessing the coupon's properties. Here is a safer version of your logic:\n\n```java\nif (coupon == null) {\n    throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Discount code not found or expired.\");\n}\nif (coupon.getExpiryDate() == null) {\n    throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Discount code has no valid expiry date.\");\n}\n// Proceed with validation...\n```\n\nThis will prevent the crash and give you a clear error message instead of a generic 500. If the problem persists, you might want to investigate your database connection pooling or caching layer",
